  "issue_number": 10996,
  "issue_title": "Parallel pylint run inflates \"Messages\" report occurrences while emitted diagnostics stay unchanged",
  "issue_body": "### Bug description\n\n```python\nWhen running pylint with multiple jobs, the final `Messages` report table can show a heavily inflated number of occurrences, while the actual emitted diagnostics stay unchanged.\n\nIn other words, the lint messages printed in the log are correct, but the aggregated report statistics at the bottom are not.\n\nThis is especially confusing in CI, because the report table suggests that the project has an order-of-magnitude larger number of violations than the actual lint output contains.\n\n### Observed behavior\n\nOn a real project, using the same input file list and the same pylint config:\n\n\npylint --rcfile=.linters/.pylintrc --persistent=no --jobs=1 $files > pylint-j1.log || true\npylint --rcfile=.linters/.pylintrc --persistent=no --jobs=4 $files > pylint-j4.log || true\n\nThe emitted missing-function-docstring diagnostics are identical:\n\n--jobs=1:\n  emitted C0116 / missing-function-docstring lines: 2084\n  Messages table occurrence count: 2084\n\n--jobs=4:\n  emitted C0116 / missing-function-docstring lines: 2084\n  Messages table occurrence count: 131819\n\nI also verified that:\n\n- the input does not include `.venv`;\n- the input does not include `site-packages`;\n- the input is an explicit list of tracked project `.py` files;\n- `--persistent=no` does not fix the inflated report count;\n- switching to `--jobs=`1 fixes the report count.\n\nSo this does not appear to be caused by pylint-cache persistence or by accidentally linting dependencies.\n```\n\n### Configuration\n\n```ini\n[MAIN]\njobs=4\npersistent=yes\n\n[REPORTS]\nreports=yes\nscore=yes\n\nThe issue is triggered by parallel execution (`jobs=4` / `--jobs=4`) when reports are enabled.\n\n`persistent=yes` is present in the project configuration, but the inflated `Messages` report is still reproduced when pylint is run with `--persistent=no`, so persistence does not appear to be the root cause.\n```\n\n### Command used\n\n```shell\n## Possible minimal reproducer\ntmpdir=\"$(mktemp -d)\"\ncd \"$tmpdir\" || exit 1\n\npython -m venv .venv\n. .venv/bin/activate\n\npip install \"pylint==4.0.1\"\n\nfor i in $(seq 1 80); do\n  cat > \"module_${i}.py\" <<'PY'\ndef first_function():\n    return 1\n\ndef second_function():\n    return 2\nPY\ndone\n\npylint \\\n  --reports=y \\\n  --persistent=no \\\n  --jobs=1 \\\n  --disable=all \\\n  --enable=missing-function-docstring \\\n  module_*.py > pylint-j1.log || true\n\npylint \\\n  --reports=y \\\n  --persistent=no \\\n  --jobs=4 \\\n  --disable=all \\\n  --enable=missing-function-docstring \\\n  module_*.py > pylint-j4.log || true\n\necho \"emitted C0116 with --jobs=1:\"\ngrep -c 'C0116:' pylint-j1.log || true\n\necho \"emitted C0116 with --jobs=4:\"\ngrep -c 'C0116:' pylint-j4.log || true\n\necho \"Messages table with --jobs=1:\"\ngrep -A20 -E 'Messages|message id' pylint-j1.log || true\n\necho \"Messages table with --jobs=4:\"\ngrep -A20 -E 'Messages|message id' pylint-j4.log || true\n```\n\n### Pylint output\n\n```python\n--jobs=4:\n\n+----------------------------+-------------+\n|message id                  |occurrences  |\n+============================+=============+\n|missing-function-docstring  |131819       |\n+----------------------------+-------------+\n\n--jobs=1:\n\n+----------------------------+-------------+\n|message id                  |occurrences  |\n+============================+=============+\n|missing-function-docstring  |2084         |\n+----------------------------+-------------+\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe occurrence count in the final `Messages` report should match the actual number of emitted diagnostics, regardless of the value of `--jobs`.\n\nFor example, if pylint emits 2084 `C0116: missing-function-docstring` diagnostics, the final report should show:\n```\nmissing-function-docstring    2084\n```\nboth with `--jobs=1` and with `--jobs=4`.\n\n## Actual behavior\nWith `--jobs=4`, pylint emits 2084 `C0116` diagnostics, but the final Messages report shows a much larger number, for example:\n```\nmissing-function-docstring    131819\n```\n\n### Pylint version\n\n```shell\npylint 4.0.5\nastroid 4.0.4\nPython 3.12.7 (main, Oct  1 2024, 02:05:46) [Clang 15.0.0 (clang-1500.3.9.4)]\n```\n\n### OS / Environment\n\nOS: Linux CI runner\nPython: 3.12\npylint: 4.0.1\nastroid: 4.0.1\nShell: bash/sh\nExecution context: GitLab CI\n\nThe issue is reproduced when pylint is run with `--jobs=4`.\nThe input is an explicit list of tracked project Python files.\n`.venv` and `site-packages` are not included.\nUsing `--jobs=1` makes the final `Messages` report count match the emitted diagnostics.\n\n### Additional dependencies\n\n```python\nNot applicable at the moment. The issue seems reproducible with a minimal pylint-only environment. I can provide the full `pip freeze` output if needed.\n```",
